{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The embedding vector produced for a given query string has the correct dimensionality for the vector database index.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"A mock embedding client can hide real model/index drift (e.g., provider model dimension change, wrong model deployment, or serialization mismatch). To catch an actual production failure boundary, the test should call the real embedding endpoint and compare returned vector length against the live index dimension.","test_description":"Run an API-level test against a real embedding service and real vector index metadata: submit a fixed query, capture the produced embedding length, read index dimension from the vector DB, and assert equality. Fail if embedding call succeeds but dimensions differ or indexing rejects the vector.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.35,"System":0.5,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The similarity search returns results ordered by descending cosine similarity score.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Ordering correctness is at the boundary between retrieval code and vector DB query semantics. A pure unit test of sorting logic can miss DB adapter behavior (metric selection, score sign, tie handling, query params). This does not require real external network if a local/vector test instance is used.","test_description":"Seed a test vector index with controlled vectors and known cosine relationships, execute the real similarity-search module, and assert returned scores are monotonic descending and IDs match expected order. Include a near-tie case to detect unstable ordering bugs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.73,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The LLM re-ranking step changes the order of at least some results compared